  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries and is typically addressed under criminal legislation. It is considered a serious financial crime that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, making it appear as if it comes from a legitimate source. Specific laws and penalties vary by jurisdiction, but money laundering is generally prosecuted as a criminal offense with potential consequences including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n2. Substantial fines\n3. Imprisonment\n4. Asset seizure\n\nMany countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations to detect and prevent such activities.",
